Parliament, Monday, 19 October 2020 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow receive a briefing from the Special Investigating Unit (SIU), Hawks and the National Prosecution Authority (NPA) on Covid-19 related cases of corruption.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows: 
	
	Date: 20 October 2020
	Time: 09:30 - 13:00
	
	Meanwhile, the Portfolio Committee on Trade and Industry will receive an update on the implementation of new legislation (Competition Act) and a briefing from the Competition Commission and Tribunal on any Covid-19 investigations and cases.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	
	Date: 20 October 2020.
	Time: 09:00 – 12:00
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES
	
